Sentencas: Analysis of recent experimental impedance spectra and polarization curves of nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni/YSZ) patterned anode of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) are used to interpret the CO electrochemical oxidation processes.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: A one dimensional (1D) comprehensive electrochemical oxidation model is proposed for the prediction of both the polarization curve and EIS spectra of a patterned anode SOFC.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: The model incorporates the ionic/electronic conductor microstructure, CO charge transfer steps, adsorption/desorption kinetics and surface diffusion processes.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: The model is used for the quantitative investigation of the cell performance as well as electrochemical impedance, and can bring a bridge for the experimental results and elementary reactions.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: The results indicated that the CO charge transfer mechanism is applicable to different temperature and polarization voltages.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: The concentration distribution of surface species near the three-phase boundary (TPB) is predicted.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: The surface concentration gradient is larger at lower temperatures and higher polarization voltages.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models

Sentencas: Thus, surface diffusion may be one of the important limiting steps at lower temperature and higher polarization voltage.
Titulo: Simulation of EIS spectra and polarization curves based on Ni/YSZ patterned anode elementary reaction models
